Comment: I accept this contribution because it is simple and effective. I've seen that it is very similar to another clash of code but I don't think that it is a problem.

‚ùå Rejected the contribution.
Comment: After reviewing the approved clash as pointed out by @kozuechan, I am of the opinion that this clash is too similar in nature, even though the vowel set is one letter ("Y") different. At the core, both clashes require the same operations performed in the same order.

If both clashes were currently pending approval (i.e., assuming the approved clash were not already approved), I would still pick the other clash due to the added complexity of handling the empty output. I understand that this makes clashes less fun to some, but I believe it's an edge case worth being thrown into the mix for the player's consideration.

‚úÖ Approved the contribution.
Comment: I is a good puzzle

Note for reviewers: This clash is similar to https://www.codingame.com/contribute/view/671710ba251f28b01d2fd4ecc723f1b9043ce. There are minor differences such as whether "Y" is treated as a vowel. I'm neutral on whether it's too similar to be rejected.
VRY STRTFRWRD ND GD FR CLSH F CD! Y SR N N HS LRDY DN THS BFR!

Constraints
* Please change "len" to "length".

* Please add comma (",") to the character set (present in Validators 4 and 5).

* Please add:
The output is never an empty string.

Cases
* These characters are missing in tests: (comma), I and U, and the uppercase letter U is missing in validators. Please either modify the existing cases or add a pair of cases with the missing characters.

Thanks.

NC N, THNK Y!
MCH PPRCTD, S LWYS. :)

M PRTTY SR NN HS DN THS BFR. BT Y'R LLWD T HV CLSHS THT R SMLR S LNG S THY RN'T DPLCTS, NYWY. BT 'V NVR SN THS CNCPT S  CLSH BFR.

Thanks for finding that. Someone else thought it might be a repeat, but I didn't think I'd seen one like it.

Makes me wonder if they got the idea from Hebrew too...

Note: similar clashes are allowed, as long as the tests and statement are different. But if you don't think this is fun then it's fine to reject it.
